text.section:
The council of unit owners or the body delegated in the bylaws of a condominium to carry out the responsibilities of the council of unit owners may adopt rules for the condominium if:
Each unit owner is mailed or delivered:
A copy of the proposed rule;
Notice that unit owners are permitted to submit written comments on the proposed rule; and
Notice of the proposed effective date of the proposed rule;
Before a vote is taken on the proposed rule, an open meeting is held to allow each unit owner or tenant to comment on the proposed rule;
The meeting held under this paragraph may not be held unless:
After notice has been given to unit owners as provided in this subsection, the proposed rule is passed at a regular or special meeting by a majority vote of those present and voting of the council of unit owners or the body delegated in the bylaws of the condominium to carry out the responsibilities of the council of unit owners.
